:: loc-county-road-6 {"position":"100,550","size":"150,100"}
County Road 6 stretches through the rural Pennsylvania countryside, a narrow two-lane blacktop road that winds between rolling hills and farmland. The asphalt is cracked and patched in places, with grass growing through the edges where maintenance has been deferred. Wooden fence posts mark property boundaries, and the occasional mailbox on a leaning post indicates the scattered rural residences. The road carries the quiet hum of distant farm machinery and the occasional pickup truck, but traffic is sparse in this remote area.
