:: loc-mainhouse-porch-north {"position":"100,700","size":"150,100"}
The northern section of the wraparound porch extends along the side of the house toward the kitchen area, offering a more private sitting area away from the main driveway. This section is furnished with a wooden porch swing that hangs from heavy chains, its cushions faded from years of weather. A small side table holds an assortment of farm-related items—work gloves, a thermos, and agricultural magazines. From here, you can see across the farm property toward the pool area and the dense forest beyond.
