:: loc-neighbors-copse {"position":"100,850","size":"150,100"}
A small grove of mixed hardwood trees creates a natural boundary between properties, serving as both windbreak and privacy screen. The copse consists primarily of oak, maple, and birch trees with dense underbrush that provides cover for wildlife. Fallen logs and leaf litter create a soft carpet underfoot, and the dappled sunlight filtering through the canopy gives the area a peaceful, secluded feeling. However, there's something unsettling about the silence here—no bird songs, no rustling of small animals, just an oppressive quiet that seems to muffle even your own footsteps.
